com.aconex.challenge.numbertowords.dictionary.transformers

Class TransformerContainer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.aconex.challenge.numbertowords.dictionary.transformers.TransformerContainer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - This is the type of the transformed element

    public class TransformerContainer<T>
extends Object
    It is a generic container class of the below different transformations that happen now in converting numbers to a word combination.
    • Presently whitespaces and punctuations are stripped from phone numbers.
    • Similarly, whitespaces and punctuations are strpped from input dictionary words, and converted to upper case.
    • Then the above dictionary word is transformed to a number to be stored in the Dictionary
    • And then eventually the above dictionary word is transformed to a possible combination of words
    To elaborate, we have phone numbers and dictionary words coming as input in a raw form and we need to apply business rules to them before they can actually be used.
    Like in phone numbers and dictionary words we need to strip of the punctuations and whitespaces.
    Ex- If an input phone number is 434-508-305, it first needs to be transformed to 434508305
    Similarly an input dictionary word like "won't" needs to be transformed to "wont" before it is added to the Dictionary
    Furthermore if the input is invalid, we can instead store the errors
    This class can also be used to store the output of finding the matching word combinations. Ex- An input number like 2255.63, based on a particular dictionary is transformed to a Set of words:: CALL-ME and BALL-ME

    aagarwal

      • flipInput

        public void flipInput()
               throws IllegalAccessException
        Utility method which would set transformed as input so that the same object can be piped to a different transformer.
        Chose to flip the input rather than creating a new container object so that the errors are not lost. And the input of the previous transform might not be of any use.
        Throws:
        IllegalAccessException - If the transformed object is not of type String
